The '''Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso''' is a car built by the French motor company [[Citro<U+00EB>n]] and first unveiled at the [[2008 Paris Motor Show]] as a [[concept car]] named "Drooneel".<ref>{{cite web|title=C3 Picasso Latin America history (Spanish)|url=http://www.viarural.com.ar/viarural.com.ar/insumosagropecuarios/ganaderos/vehiculos/citroen/c3-picasso/default.htm|work=Infosite for Argentina vehicles|publisher=ViaRural.com.ar|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref> [[Donato Coco]] and [[Jean-Pierre Plou<U+00E9>]] designed the vehicle. The Picasso is a [[front-wheel drive]], [[mini MPV|mini multi-purpose vehicle (MPV)]] version of the [[Citro<U+00EB>n C3]] and successor to the [[Citro<U+00EB>n Xsara Picasso]], designed to compete with the [[Opel Meriva|Opel/Vauxhall Meriva]], [[Nissan Note]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/|title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso competitors |publisher=Parkers |date= |author= |accessdate=16 May 2012}}</ref> [[Renault Modus]] and the [[Ford Fusion (Europe)|Ford Fusion]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citroenet.org.uk/passenger-cars/psa/c3/c3-picasso/c3-picasso23.html|title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso competitors |publisher=Citro<U+00EB>n<U+00EB>t |date= |author= |accessdate=18 May 2012}}</ref> The vehicle has been adapted for an "Urban-off-road" appearance for the Latin America market, where it has been sold as the [[Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Aircross]] since 2010.

The first C3 Picasso was assembled in December 2007 at the [[PSA Trnava Plant]] in west Slovakia, which Citro<U+00EB>n announced from France in July 2008 would be the sole manufacturer of the model. Citro<U+00EB>n presented the finished product to the Slovak press and public on 25 September before it was unveiled to the world in October at the 2008 Paris Motor Show. The Trnava Plant was expected to produce 28 cars per hour as the C3 Picasso went on sale in France in February 2009 for {{currency|14,950|Eur}}. The company began to sell the car in other European markets in March 2009.<ref name="French Review and price">{{cite web |url=http://www.samar.pl/__/3/3.a/17755?locale=en_EN |title=French review and price |publisher=Rafal Zaglewski |date=5 December 2008|accessdate=19 April 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Slovakia plant and production information|url=http://s3.amazonaws.com/zanran_storage/www.psa-peugeot-citroen.com/ContentPages/24437781.pdf|work=Trnava production information leaflet|publisher=PSA Peugeot Citro<U+00EB>n|accessdate=14 August 2012}}</ref> 

When launched in Spain in 2009, only three trims were available: LX, SX, or Exclusive. The LX was the most basic and least expensive model, with a {{convert|95|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} VTi engine, priced at {{currency|12,590|Eur}}, while the Exclusive model was most expensive with a {{convert|110|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} HDi ''Airdream'' engine at {{currency|18,650|Eur}}.<ref>{{cite web|last=Costas|first=Javier|title=Car news (Spanish)|url=http://www.motorpasion.com/citroen/citroen-c3-picasso-precios-motores-y-equipamiento-en-espana|work=Car news for the Spanish market|publisher=motorpasion.com|accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref> The C3 Picasso was launched in the United Kingdom on 9 April 2009, where it went on sale for {{currency|11,495|GBP}} for the 1.4-litre VTi, the most basic model with {{convert|44|mpgimp|L/100 km mpgus|abbr=on}},<ref name="autozine1">{{cite web|author=Wan, Mark |url=http://www.autozine.org/Archive/Citroen/new/C3_Picasso.html |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso |publisher=Autozine.org |date=25 May 2009 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-news/citroen-c3-picasso-prices/237361 |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso prices&nbsp;<U+2013> Car and Car-Buying News |work=whatcar.com |date=27 January 2009 |author= |accessdate=28 March 2012}}</ref> while the most expensive was the 'Exclusive' with a 1.6-litre HDi engine and {{convert|62|mpgimp|L/100 km mpgus|abbr=on}} at {{currency|15,595|GBP}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cars.uk.msn.com/reviews/articles.aspx?cp-documentid=147874191 |title=C3 Picasso review |author=Ian Dickson |publisher=Msn Cars |date=29 January 2009 |accessdate=30 March 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/facts-and-figures/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/42480/ |title=1.6HDi Exclusive facts and figures |publisher=Parkers |accessdate=30 March 2012 }}</ref> A redesigned version of the car was shown at the [[2012 Paris Motor Show]] on 27 September 2012 and was on sale in Europe by November.<ref name="Facelift launched in Spain"/>

== Models ==
Variations of the models exist for different markets and times, with a range of engine options, features, and extras. 

*'''Exclusive''' is consistently the most expensive trim for each market, with the biggest choice of engines and features. It is the only model to feature a folding front passenger seat, making the storage space into the whole interior of the car except the driver's seat. Extras for the trim include: tinted windows, rear parking sensors, automatic windscreen wipers, a leather and chrome interior, and dual-zone automatic climate control and pollen filter, which allows for two varying temperature settings simultaneously in the vehicle.<ref name="Parkers C3 Picasso Exclusive storage"/>

===Limited and Special Edition===
*'''Blackcherry''' is a [[Special edition|limited edition]] trim, available in the UK since November 2010 and based on the VTR+. It was sold with the 1.6-litre High-pressure Direct Injection (HDi) diesel engine.<ref name="C3 Picasso Blackcherry Autotrader">{{cite web|title=Auto Trader review the Blackcherry|url=http://www.autotrader.co.uk/articles/2010/11/cars/citroen/c3-picasso/citroen-c3-picasso-special-edition-unveiled|work=02 November 2010|publisher=Auto Trader|accessdate=16 August 2012}}</ref> It was discontinued and replaced with the Code Red and Code White in January 2012, which have the same engine.<ref name="C3 Picasso Code Red and White" />
*'''90th Anniversary'''; the release of the Limited Edition 90th Anniversary C3 Picasso in August 2009 was the UK's third limited edition model. It was created to commemorate 90 years of Citro<U+00EB>n and has similar features to the Exclusive trim, sold at the same price and features the ''MyWay'' SatNav system, leather upholstery, and a commemorative badge on the dashboard emblazoned with the wording "90 Years". As bonus, it came equipped with {{currency|1,000|GBP}} of extras and was released in an advertising campaign of Anniversary trims for other Citro<U+00EB>n models at the same time as the launch of the Limited Edition Millennium trim in France.<ref>{{cite news|title=C3 Picasso 90th Anniversary and the extras|url=http://www.autoevolution.com/news/new-limited-edition-from-citroen-c3-picasso-9426.html|accessdate=15 November 2012|newspaper=autoevolution.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=What Car on the 90th Anniversary model|url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-news/citroen-c3-picasso-special-edition/242037|work=Car Reviewer and news site|publisher=WhatCar|accessdate=4 September 2012}}</ref> The model was limited to 150 cars in the UK, of which only one has been sold and registered for use.<ref>{{cite web|author=Smith, Olly |url=http://howmanyleft.co.uk/vehicle/citroen_c3_picasso_exc_90_anv_hdi |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso 90th Anniversary <U+2013> How Many Left |publisher=Howmanyleft.co.uk |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> 
*'''Millennium'''; several  trims were released in France under the Millennium moniker, including the: C1, C4, C4 Picasso, C5 and C5 Tourer. The model has 16-inch (41 cm) alloy wheels, the ''MyWay'' SatNav system and radio with built-in [[Bluetooth]] and dual-zone automatic climate control. The car was available in a metallic or pearlescent finish.<ref name="Citro<U+00EB>n Millennium series range (French)">{{cite web|title=Citro<U+00EB>n Millennium series range (French)|url=http://blog.le-parnass.com/catalogue_pdf/serie%20speciale%20millenium.pdf|work=Car variation specs|publisher=Citro<U+00EB>n|accessdate=19 October 2012}}</ref>
*'''Code Red/Code White''' released in In January 2012, the limited edition C3 Picasso Code red and Code white replaced the Blackcherry in the UK.<ref name="C3 Picasso Blackcherry Autotrader" /> The Code has the same engine as the Blackcherry and has been finely tuned for a marginally increased [[fuel economy in automobiles|fuel economy]] and lower carbon dioxide ({{CO2}}) emissions. It features obsidian black bumpers and 17-inch (43 cm) Polar White or Cherry Red "clover" alloy wheels, and can be equipped with extra features, which include roof bars, curtain airbags, cruise control and a speed limiter. Body colours exclusive to the trim are Belle Ile Blue, Shark Grey and Cherry Red.<ref name="C3 Picasso Code Red and White">{{cite web|title=C3 Picasso Code debut|url=http://www.expertreviews.co.uk/car-tech/1289323/citro-n-c3-picasso-gets-a-code-upgrade|work=news source and reviewer and seller of common buys|publisher=Expertreviews.co.uk|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref><ref name="C3 Picasso Code brochure">{{cite web|title=C3 Picasso Code brochure|url=http://info.citroen.co.uk/Assets/pdf/new-cars/c3-picasso-code/brochure.pdf|publisher=Citro<U+00EB>n UK|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref>
*'''Passion Bleus''' was released in France to celebrate the [[UEFA Euro 2012|2012 European Football Championship]]. The name is a tribute to the French national football team, which Citro<U+00EB>n supports as a partner of the [[French Football Federation]]. The advertising campaign for the Passion Bleus involved French footballers, [[rallying]] champion [[S<U+00E9>bastien Loeb]], and an online [[Facebook]] game "Le Pilote et le Bleu" (The Pilot and Blue). Other Citro<U+00EB>n vehicles to receive a Passion Bleus trim were the: C1, C3, C4, C4 Picasso, and the Berlingo Multispace.<ref>{{cite web|title=Passion Bleus released in France|url=http://www.citroen.fr/actualites/passion-bleus/|work=Creator|publisher=CITRO<U+00CB>N|accessdate=6 December 2012}}</ref>

==Design and features==
[[File:Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso rear 20100411.jpg|(100px)px|thumbnail|right|The rear of the C3 Picasso]]
All C3 Picasso models have an [[anti-lock braking system]] (ABS), [[Electronic brakeforce distribution]] (EBD), child locks, [[Remote keyless system|remote central locking]] and two front airbags.<ref name="Autotrader1">{{cite web | url = http://www.autotrader.co.uk/articles/2009/03/cars/citroen/c3-picasso/citroen-c3-picasso-1-6-vti-car-review |title=C3 Picasso review |publisher=Autotrader |date= 23 March 2009|accessdate=28 May 2012}}</ref> The vehicle is only available as a 5-seater, but with all models the three rear seats can be folded flat to increase the [[Trunk (automobile)|boot]] capacity from {{convert|385|l|cuft}} or {{convert|500|l|cuft}} including the hidden compartment to store the parcel shelf, up to a maximum of {{convert|1,506|l|cuft}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.topgear.com/uk/citroen/c3-picasso/verdict|title=Top Gear review |publisher=Topgear.com |date= |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carpages.co.uk/citroen/citroen-c3-picasso-review-part-1-09-06-09.asp|title=Car Pages review |publisher=Carpages.co.uk |date=9 June 2012 |accessdate=23 April 2012}}</ref> The Exclusive model features a folding front passenger seat to increase the storage space further.<ref name="Parkers C3 Picasso Exclusive storage">{{cite web|url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/comfort/ |title=New Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso (09 on) Car Review&nbsp;<U+2013> Comfort |publisher=Parkers |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name="Autotrader1"/> All models in the range have a "Mistral Maxi Taylor" woven cloth interior; according to Citro<U+00EB>n, top European engineers and designers including  [[Donato Coco]] and [[Jean-Pierre Plou<U+00E9>]] were involved in designing the vehicle.<ref name="21 cars you can't drive in the US"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Citro<U+00EB>n uses "top designers" and engineers|url=http://www.cmhcitroen.co.za/new-citroen/C3/citroen-C3.aspx|work=Seller of Citro<U+00EB>n vehicles|publisher=CMH Group|accessdate=8 August 2012}}</ref>

Optional accessories are available for the range, including an aluminium roof rack capable of carrying {{convert|60|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} and kerbside lights in the door mirrors. Also available are: {{convert|16|in|cm|adj=on}} and {{convert|17|in|cm|adj=on}} alloy wheels with a choice of two patterns, chrome mouldings for the bumpers and doors, front fog lamps and cruise control, rear parking sensors, automatic lights (standard on some variants), [[Electronic stability control|Electronic Stability Control (ESC)]] and a [[Speed limiter|speed limitation device]]{{spaced ndash}}which are commonly used for safety reasons or to reduce fuel bills.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.citroen.co.uk/new-cars/car-range/citroen-c3-picasso/#/new-cars/car-range/citroen-c3-picasso/exterior/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso &#124; Car Range &#124; Citro<U+00EB>n UK |publisher=Citro<U+00EB>n |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>
A seatbelt reminder, which can be added to the passenger and rear seats, is fitted to the driver's seat as standard.<ref name="EuroNCAP344"/><ref>{{cite web|last=Walker|first=Steve|title=C3 Picasso video review|url=http://motoring.friday-ad.co.uk/car-reviews/video/new/Citroen-C3_Picasso/id/8013/|work=sales and reviews|publisher=Friday-Ad|accessdate=10 August 2012}}</ref>

The chassis platform used for the C3 Picasso is a modified version of that in the [[Citro<U+00EB>n C3]] and the [[Peugeot 207]], giving it a comparable wheelbase.<ref>{{cite web|title=Autoblog Argentina Aircross review|url=http://translate.google.co.uk/translate?hl=en&sl=es&u=http://autoblog.com.ar/2011/01/critica-citroen-c3-aircross-1-6-16v/&prev=/search%3Fq%3DC3%2BPICASSO%2BAIRCROSS%26hl%3Den%26client%3Dfirefox-a%26rls%3Dorg.mozilla:en-US:official%26channel%3Ds%26biw%3D1024%26bih%3D637%26prmd%3Dimvns&sa=X&ei=120qUKKWKJLB0gW_o4HYBA&ved=0CHkQ7gEwBw|work=Autoblog|publisher=Autoblog Argentina|accessdate=14 August 2012}}</ref> The reuse of automobile platforms is commonplace, especially for Citro<U+00EB>n because the Trnava plant builds the Peugeot 207 and the C3 Picasso. The parent company [[PSA Peugeot Citro<U+00EB>n]] pools resources and manufacturing for some vehicles, and sometimes [[Badge engineering|rebadges]] vehicles, combining design teams between two or more brands to create a shared product.<ref name="Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro<U+00EB>n"/> The advantage is the designing and testing vehicles at a reduced cost for the participating brands, but creates multiple, identical-looking vehicles for the market, sometimes with minor styling differences. Examples include: the [[Fiat Scudo]], [[Peugeot Expert]] and [[Citro<U+00EB>n Jumpy|Citro<U+00EB>n Dispatch]], the [[Toyota Aygo]], [[Peugeot 107]] and [[Citro<U+00EB>n C1]], and the [[Peugeot Partner]] and [[Citro<U+00EB>n Berlingo]]. Citro<U+00EB>n placed a contractual obligation on the manufacturers to use [[Environmentally friendly|green materials]] for the C3 Picasso range. These comprise <U+2265>11% of the {{convert|170|kg|abbr=on|1}} of polymers on the vehicle, including the mudguards, parcel shelf and boot carpet.<ref name="Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro<U+00EB>n"/> Citro<U+00EB>n recommends the vehicle is serviced at least every two years, or at every {{convert|20,000|miles|km}} for petrol models and {{convert|12,500|miles|km}} for the HDi diesel models.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carmagazine.co.uk/Drives/Search-Results/Long-term-tests/Citroen-C3-Picasso-16-HDI-long-term-test-review/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso 1.6 HDi long-term test review |publisher=Carmagazine.co.uk |date=15 March 2010 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref>

===Engines===
When equipped with the 1.6-litre VTi engine, the C3 Picasso Exclusive and VTR+ models are capable of a top speed of {{convert|117|mi/h|km/h|abbr=on}} in 10.6 seconds and {{convert|120|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}. This 1.6 litre and a smaller 1.4 litre VTi petrol engine, were developed by PSA Peugeot Citro<U+00EB>n and [[BMW]], along with a 1.6 L diesel engine and the two 1.6 L HDi ''Airdream'' engines. Every model came with a 5-speed manual gearbox until 2011, when 6-speed manual and automatic (EGS6) manual versions were introduced,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/facts-and-figures/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/53872/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso (09 on) 1.6 VTi 16v Exclusive 5d EGS6 |publisher=Parkers |date=1 November 2011 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/facts-and-figures/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/42475/ | title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso (09 on) 1.4 VTi 16v Exclusive|publisher=Parkers |date=1 November 2011 |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> along with an eco-friendly [[start-stop system]] and [[regenerative braking]] technology in certain models, notably the Exclusive and Tendance models for the German market.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/facts-and-figures/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso Parkers model lineup |publisher=Parkers |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref name="On and off the road figures for the UK">{{cite web|author=Smith, Olly|url=http://howmanyleft.co.uk/?q=c3+picasso|title=On and off the road figures in the UK |publisher=How Many Left with information from the DVLA |date= |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref> According to Citro<U+00EB>n, these two new features reduce {{CO2}} emissions significantly<ref name="Prices, Technical data and Equipment PDF (German)" /> and their introduction coincided with the release of a higher specification ''Airdream'' engine, the [[European emission standards|European emission standards (Euro 5)]] carbon dioxide emissions limits were lowered and the addition of [[low-rolling resistance tires|low-rolling resistance tyres]] were added to the entire range. The tyres are specially designed to minimize wasted energy when the tyre rolls and have been estimated by the [[California Energy Commission]] to save 1.5<U+2013>4.5% of fuel in a typical car.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carsuk.net/citroen-c3-picasso-blackcherry-2011-updates/|title=C3 Picasso engines tweaked to be Euro 5 compliant |publisher=Cars UK |date=28 October 2010 |accessdate=9 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.energy.ca.gov/reports/2003-01-31_600-03-001F-VOL1.PDF |title=California State Fuel-Efficient Tire Report: Volume I |publisher=California Energy Commission |date=January 2003 |accessdate=11 August 2007}}</ref>

At first Citro<U+00EB>n decided not to offer their new automatic EGS6 gearbox version in the UK due to the unfavourable exchange rate and costs, although this changed after a small number were privately imported for insurance classification purposes. The EGS6 gearbox became an option for the 1.6 L VTi engine models shortly after.<ref>{{cite web|title=Howards Citro<U+00EB>n - Taunton on the EGS6 in the UK|url=http://www.howardstaunton.citroen.co.uk/about-us/offers/pre-reg-c3-picasso-exclusive-egs-e-hdi-only-1449/?newsId=657151|work=Car Sales and information|publisher=Howards Citro<U+00EB>n|accessdate=27 September 2012}}</ref> The complete vehicle lineup includes multiple models and engine configurations, all with different specifications and tuning:
