==Safety==
{{Euro NCAP
|year=2009
|align=right
|overall_stars=4
|description=5 door [[Left hand drive|LHD]] MPV
|reference_name=EuroNCAP344
|reference_code=344
|adult_points=86
|adult_percent=81 |child_points=37
|child_percent=76
|pedestrian_points=16
|pedestrian_percent=43
|safety_points=3 |safety_percent=40}}
[[Euro NCAP|The European New Car Assessment Programme]] (Euro NCAP) tested a C3 Picasso Confort {{convert|90|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} model with standard equipment, including: a single forward airbag for each front seat, a [[Speed limiter|speed limitation device]], but no ESC. The vehicle was scored on the basis of: child and adult injury, including [[Whiplash (medicine)|whiplash]] risk from the seating, a pedestrian front impact rating, safety equipment and clear labels detailing how to disable some features. The results of the front end tests were mixed, with the bumper scoring all available points, but the vehicle was penalised for the lack of protection and the potential damage caused if a pedestrian is struck by the bonnet. Protection inside the car was scored highly for almost every seat, and for adult and child protection; it lost points for its use of forward-facing restraints, which can be fatal in an accident if an infant is hit by an airbag. The C3 Picasso was also penalised for offering very poor whiplash protection in the driver's seat{{spaced ndash}}scoring nothing in two of the three tests and then losing points for the position of the unadjusted restraint. Overall, the vehicle scored four of five stars, less than most vehicles the Euro NCAP compares it with, which were released around the same time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Euro NCAP C3 Picasso safety comparison list of vehicles|url=http://www.euroncap.com/viewcomparable.aspx?car=87f48403-a58e-4323-ade8-ffbe82baa951|work=Car safety reviewer|publisher=Euro NCAP|accessdate=14 September 2012}}</ref>

===Recalls and ''Watchdog'' investigation===

On 20 June 2010, 611 C3 Picassos built between January and March 2010 were recalled due to incorrectly routed fuel pipes, which were believed to have been in contact with the heat shield. This fault may have caused chafing and may lead to a fuel leak. The models were built between January and March 2010 and were sold in the UK.<ref name="The AA lists the UK recalls">{{cite web|title=The AA lists the UK recalls|url=http://www.theaa.com/allaboutcars/recalls/recalls.jsp?modelID=AJ&modelName=C3+Picasso&makeName=Citroen&makeId=A7|work=Motoring organization|publisher=The AA|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> On 24 August 2010, all 13,234 Picassos sold in the UK<ref name="On and off the road figures for the UK" /> were recalled because the windscreen trim could deteriorate, and could eventually detach, leading to a loose-fitting windscreen.<ref name="The AA lists the UK recalls" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Department for Transport windscreen trim recall|url=http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Bulletin%2072.pdf|work=Department for Transport|publisher=Department for Transport|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref>

In May 2011, all 24,091 C3 Picassos in the UK were recalled for a safety modification,<ref>{{cite web|title=Department for Transport Picasso recall (page 11)|url=http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Bulletin%2073.pdf|work=Department for Transport|publisher=Department for Transport|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> following complaints and an investigation by BBC consumer affairs programme ''[[Watchdog (TV series)|Watchdog]]'' into brakes that could be activated on the passenger side of the right-hand drive vehicles.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-13446522 |title=BBC News&nbsp;<U+2013> Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso UK recall over 'passenger brake' |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=19 May 2011 |accessdate=27 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-13446522 | work=BBC News | title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso UK recall over 'passenger brake' | date=19 May 2011}}</ref>
The problem occurred because of the way the vehicles were modified for right-hand-drive. The investigation showed that although the brake pedal had been moved to the right, it was still connected to a mechanism on the passenger side. This was covered by felt carpet and meant that both the front passenger and driver could activate the brakes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-13447395 |title=BBC News&nbsp;<U+2013> Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso UK recall over 'passenger brake' |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=19 May 2011 |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banwells.co.uk/news/bbc-watchdog-citroen-c3-picasso-recall-further-information/|title=C3 Picasso recall announcement by Banwells Automotive |publisher=Banwells Automotive |date=19 May 2011 |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref> A further investigation by ''Watchdog'' later found the same problem in other Citro<U+00EB>n models and some vehicles produced by Renault and Peugeot, some of which were registered in 2002. All three manufacturers worked with the [[Vehicle and Operator Services Agency]] (VOSA) to identify the severity of the problem but no vehicles were found to be affected enough to issue recalls.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rizi|first=Elham|title=Watchdog investigation finds more models affected|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/watchdog/2011/05/brake-ing_news_update.html|accessdate=24 August 2012|date=31 May 2011}}</ref> 

8,815 Picassos built between January and May 2011 for the UK market were recalled on 2 September 2011 when it was discovered that the battery cable was too short and could cause gearbox failures and in turn stall the engine. The faulty earth return cable was replaced.<ref>{{cite web|title=The AA lists the UK recalls (page 2)|url=http://www.theaa.com/allaboutcars/recalls/recalls.jsp?&makeName=Citroen&modelID=AJ&modelName=C3+Picasso&makeId=A7&lowIndex=3|work=Motoring organization|publisher=The AA|accessdate=13 August 2012}}</ref> Despite the recalls, the vehicle continued to sell well in the UK and has won numerous awards.<ref name="On and off the road figures for the UK" />

==Reviews==
[[File:Citroen C3 Picasso Exclusive Belle-Ile-Blau Interieur.JPG|thumb|Reviews of the hard plastic interior were mostly negative.]]

Critics praised the  praised Citroen C3 Picasso in reviews for its ergonomics, [[Bauhaus]]-inspired styling,<ref>{{cite web|author=Car Reviews |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/motoring/carreviews/4640625/Citron-C3-Picasso-review.html |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso review |work=The Telegraph |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> ease of use and the amount of space offered, many reviewers criticised the interior, which they said  felt "cheap". The quality and reliability of the petrol engines was criticised by most reviewers as "sluggish" and struggling to carry the weight of the vehicle, although the diesel engines feedback was more positive as they are able to cope much better and run smoother. Reviewers' comment about the tight turning radius of the vehicle were favourable . The combination of the panoramic three-part windscreen, thin door pillars and high seats, which together increase the visibility of the road{{spaced ndash}}led one reviewer to compare it with a greenhouse.<ref name="French Review and price" /><ref>{{cite web|last=McAlpine|first=Craig|title=C3 Picasso review: like a greenhouse|url=http://www.carbuyer.co.uk/archive/citroen-c3-picasso-16-vti-review|work=A car review site|publisher=Carbuyer.co.uk|accessdate=8 August 2012}}</ref> 

The car has three monitors on the dashboard, the first monitors the status of important components, while the second controls the sound system, and the last is a rev counter, digital speedometer and the fuel gauge. ''Cnet'' described the speed gauge monitor as clear and "close to the driver's natural line of sight", but criticized the other two monitors for being unreadable and possibly dangerous if used by the driver while the car is moving.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hide|first=Nick|title=Cnet reviews the C3 Picasso|url=http://reviews.cnet.co.uk/cars/citroen-c3-picasso-review-49301805/|work=News and review site|publisher=Cnet|accessdate=23 August 2012}}</ref> Some reviewers complained about the vehicle's soundproofing, with the loudness of the wind complained about. The engine at high speed received mixed reviews, while a number of reviewers reported a fault with the screenwash bottle, which can freeze in cold weather and blow a fuse when used.<ref name="autozine1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parkers.co.uk/cars/reviews/citroen/c3-picasso/estate-2009/ |title=New Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso (09 on) Car Review&nbsp;<U+2013> Summary |publisher=Parkers |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Brown, Mike |url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-reviews/citroen/c3-picasso-mpv/summary/25842-7/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso Mpv Review &#124; What Car? |publisher=Whatcar.com |date= |accessdate=31 March 2012}}</ref> The reviewer for [[European Car of the Year]] 2010 called the nominated C3 Picasso fuel efficient, but said it had "dull steering".<ref>{{cite web|title=European Car of the year nominee|url=http://www.caroftheyear.org/nominees/2010_1/coty|work=Car reviewer for awards|publisher=European Car of the year|accessdate=15 November 2012}}</ref>

===Awards===
UK publication ''[[Top Gear Magazine]]'' awarded the C3 Picasso "Family Car of the Year" in 2008, stating "This is what a 21st century family car should look like". Michael Harvey, the Editorial Director of the magazine admitted they had taken a chance as the model was not available in the United Kingdom until the following year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.motortorque.com/news/auto-0811/citroen-c3-picasso-wins-top-gear-family-car-gong.asp |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso wins Top Gear family car gong |publisher=MotorTorque |date= |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref>
In 2009 when the car was finally launched the awards increased, first with "Best MPV" at ''What Diesel'''s Car of the Year Awards,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.carpages.co.uk/citroen/citroen-c3-picasso-05-08-09.asp |title=The Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso Named Supermini MPV of The Year |publisher=Carpages.co.uk |date= |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref> "Scottish MPV of the Year" at the [[Scottish Car of the Year Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thevervecoatbridge.citroen.co.uk/about-us/dealer-news/citroens-c3-picasso-named-scottish-mpv-of-the-ye/?newsid=494560 |title=The Verve&nbsp;<U+2013> Coatbridge&nbsp;<U+2013> Citro<U+00EB>n's C3 Picasso named "Scottish MPV of the Year" |publisher=Thevervecoatbridge.citroen.co.uk |date= |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref> "Best Supermini MPV of the year" at "Auto Express New Car Awards"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/carreviews/new_car_awards_2009/239737/citroen_c3_picasso.html |title=C3 Picasso named best supermini-MPV |publisher=Auto Express |month=August | year=2009 |accessdate=30 March 2012}}</ref> and finally "Design of the Year" at the [[Fleet World Honours]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.carpages.co.uk/citroen/citroen-c3-picasso-05-08-09.asp |title=C3 Picasso named supermini MPV of the year |publisher=Carpages.co.uk |date=5 August 2009 |accessdate=30 March 2012}}</ref>
The [[J. D. Power and Associates|''JD Power'']] survey in 2011 announced the C3 Picasso as the best MPV on the market, with a satisfaction rating of 83.1% and five stars overall, but with the lowest rating given to the exterior quality at three stars. Many reviewers had complained of poor fitting and the finish used on the exterior.<ref>{{cite news|title=JD Power survey MPV winner 2011|url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-news/jd-power-survey-2011/mpv-winner/257096/|accessdate=8 August 2012|date=27 May 2011}}</ref>

==Advertising==
Citro<U+00EB>n's C3 Picasso advertisement was called "DOG"; it was created by [[H Suresnes]] advertising agency in France and released in June 2010. The advertisement shows a dog made up of various items, including a purse, swimming goggles, blow-dryer and shoes, wandering around the streets to the song "Somebody Come And Play" by [[Joe Raposo|Joseph G Raposo]]. In the last scene the dog is invited into the boot of a C3 Picasso by a family leaving for a holiday; the dog fits into the car with enough space to seat everyone comfortably.<ref>{{cite web|author=DOG |url=http://www.advertolog.com/citroen/adverts/dog-13756255/ |title=DOG&nbsp;<U+2013> Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso TV Commercial Ad |publisher=Advertolog.com |date= |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref> The advertisement was shown in the French market using the English-language song "Somebody Come and Play" by [[Joe Raposo]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dragtimes Dog Advertismement|url=https://dragtimes.com/video-viewer.php?v=r4XwfYST0UY&feature|work=Advertising information|publisher=Dragtimes|accessdate=13 January 2013}}</ref>

Another advertisement for the vehicle range was "Ghostbusters Reloaded", which was produced by [[Euro RSCG Paris]]. It shows three futuristic [[Ghostbusters (franchise)|Ghostbusters]] in a C3 Picasso battling a monster in the style of the ''Ghostbuters'' character [[Stay Puft Marshmallow Man]]. The monster is the size of a tall building and is made up of items including bicycles, suitcases and tyres. As the monster is defeated, it disassembles and the items fit into the boot of the Picasso. The music used is a remix of the [[Ray Parker, Jr.|Ray Parker]] [[Ghostbusters (song)|Ghostbusters theme tune]] performed by the [[Street Life DJs]]. The advertisement's strapline is; "The New Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso: The Spacebox".<ref>{{cite web|author=by Keith |url=http://www.tvadmusic.co.uk/2009/03/citroen-c3-picasso-ghostbusters-reloaded/ |title=Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso&nbsp;<U+2013> The Spacebox / Ghostbusters Reloaded |publisher=TV Ad Music |date=19 March 2009 |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Alex Brownsell |url=http://www.marketingmagazine.co.uk/news/891476/Citroen-uses-Ghostbusters-themed-ad-launch-C3-Picasso/?DCMP=ILC-SEARCH |title=Citro<U+00EB>n uses Ghostbusters-themed ad to launch C3 Picasso&nbsp;<U+2013> Marketing news |publisher=Marketing magazine |date=17 March 2009 |accessdate=19 April 2012}}</ref>

=={{Anchor|C3 Picasso facelift}}2012 Facelift==

[[File:Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso facelift (front).JPG|thumb|The C3 Picasso facelift at the [[2012 Paris Motor Show]]]]

The facelift of the Citro<U+00EB>n C3 Picasso appeared first at the [[2012 Paris Motor Show]] on 27 September.<ref>{{cite news|last=Gnaticov|first=Cristian|title=Inautonews.com on the MK2|url=http://www.inautonews.com/citroen-c3-picasso-facelift-revealed-going-to-paris-motor-show#.UFg1qq4wDMo|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=17 September 2012}}</ref> The ''eMyWay'' SatNav system located on the central console has more functionality, allowing connection to a reversing camera (available as an extra), which displays on the console's screen, LED daytime running lamps and fog lamps with built-in cornering lamps which illuminate the roadside are non-standard features on this model.<ref>{{cite web|last=Arnaldo|first=Mario|title=Msn Motor on C3 Picasso facelift|url=http://motor.es.msn.com/coches/el-nuevo-citro%C3%ABn-c3-picasso-llega-a-espa%C3%B1a|work=News and information|publisher=Msn Motor|accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref> Citro<U+00EB>n released two new exterior paint colour options; "Pearlescent white" and "Ink blue" were available for this vehicle.  It also features a chrome chevron badge on the front, giving the appearance of a crown. The facelifted vehicle range was expected to be available in the UK in the first half of 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=NewCarNet on the new C3 Picasso|url=http://www.newcarnet.co.uk/Citroen_news.html?id=12366|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=17 September 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=McIlroy|first=John|title=Whatcar on the announcement of the MK2|url=http://www.whatcar.com/car-news/new-citroen-c3-picasso-revealed/263882|accessdate=18 September 2012|date=17 September 2012}}</ref>

The model for the Spanish market was launched in November 2012 with four trim choices, the least expensive being the Attraction with a {{convert|95|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} VTi engine at {{currency|12,250|Eur}} and the most expensive being the Exclusive with a {{convert|115|bhp|kW PS|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} HDi engine at {{currency|18,475|Eur}}.<ref name="Facelift launched in Spain">{{cite web|last=Garcia|first=Enrique|title=Autoblog Spain facelift launched (Spanish)|url=http://es.autoblog.com/2012/11/05/espana-el-renovado-citroen-c3-picasso-ya-a-la-venta/|work=New site, reviews, events|publisher=Autoblog Spain|accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AutoBild.es on the new Picasso (Spanish)|url=http://www.autobild.es/noticias/citroen-c3-picasso-salon-paris-188192|work=Car news, reviews and information|publisher=Auto Bild.es|accessdate=12 November 2012}}</ref>
{{clear}}

